  },
  {
    icon: '💎',
    title: 'Trading Assistant',
    en: 'Multi-Chain Wallet & Bridge',
    bullets: [
      'Multi-chain wallets: EVM family + Solana',
      'Cross-chain bridge: HTLC atomic swap + messaging',
      'zk-SNARK / zk-STARK generated locally',
      'DAO governance v2 · quadratic voting · treasury',
    ],
  },
];

const everyday = [
  { icon: '📄', title: 'Document Conversion', example: 'Batch Word → PDF / Word → Markdown' },
  { icon: '🎬', title: 'Media Processing', example: 'Compress video, extract audio, transcode' },
  { icon: '📊', title: 'Data Analysis', example: 'CSV / Excel analysis + chart generation' },
  { icon: '🖼️', title: 'Image Processing', example: 'Batch compress, OCR text extraction' },
  { icon: '🔎', title: 'Web Research', example: 'Auto-search and summarize results' },
  { icon: '🧰', title: 'System Admin', example: 'Disk analysis, process audit, network test' },
];

const highlights = [
  {
    tag: 'v5.0.3.134 · 2026-07-03',
    title: 'CLI OAuth command-injection fix + MCP list hardening + workflow resume re-drive (security patch reaches on-device)',
    sub: 'chainlesschain 0.162.148 published to npm and bundled into the Android in-app cc (binariesVersion 20260703 / USR_VERSION 74). Desktop + CLI users covered via npm; Android on-device users via this APK release.',
    desc: 'CLI OAuth openBrowser cmd.exe command injection (HIGH, remote-influenced): mcp-oauth opened the authorize page with spawn("cmd",["/c","start","",url]) — the & in the OAuth query string reached cmd.exe, truncating the URL at the first & and executing the remainder as commands; the authorize URL derives from remote MCP server metadata, so a malicious server could run arbitrary Windows commands. Now http(s)-only via new URL() + rundll32 url.dll,FileProtocolHandler (plain exe, verbatim argv, no shell); +4 regression tests. MCP server-list corrupt-row hardening: _rowToConfig used bare JSON.parse(row.args||"[]") (guards NULL, not a corrupt value), so one bad row took down the whole cc mcp servers / auto-connect — now routed through safeJsonParse; +1 test. Desktop workflow-engine resume: resumeExecution previously only flipped status without re-driving → breakpoint/approval workflows stuck forever while the IPC reported success, approval "waiting" wholly unresumable, executeWorkflow overwrote the paused status with completed → now derives the frontier from execution.log + dag, re-drives remaining stages, steps over the paused breakpoint once, treats an approval resume as granted; +9 tests. Versions: productVersion v5.0.3.133 → v5.0.3.134; chainlesschain 0.162.148 published to npm; USR_VERSION 74 / binariesVersion 20260703.',
  },
  {
    tag: 'v5.0.3.133 · 2026-06-28',
    title: 'PDH collection/analysis trio: MIUI browser history + bill-month/timeline fixes + Weibo DMs',
    sub: 'Cumulative v5.0.3.131–133: MIUI/AOSP default-browser history collector; two PDH analysis-layer date-correctness fixes shipped on device; Weibo direct-message collection (device-verified schema, high-sensitivity opt-in). pdh 0.4.36 → 0.4.39 + cli 0.162.117 → 0.162.129 published to npm; Android cc bundle internal-binaries-android-v20260628c (USR_VERSION 61).',
    desc: 'v5.0.3.131 MIUI/AOSP browser-history collector: new browser-history-aosp adapter reads com.android.browser browser2.db (history / bookmarks, columns resolved dynamically via PRAGMA table_info for ROM-variant safety), reusing the Chrome adapter normalize() to emit identical BROWSE Event / LINK Item — closing the "adaptation gap" the schema dictionary recorded for MIUI default browser. v5.0.3.132 PDH analysis date fixes on device: deriving the bill month from dueDate used a naive setMonth(getMonth()-1) that overflowed to the wrong month for due-days 29–31 (now new Date(year, month-1, 1)); an explicit sinceMonths timeline window was silently masked by the default 7-day window (now the default only applies when no window is given); new bridge-connect integration test (6 tests) automating the cross-device verification flow. v5.0.3.133 Weibo DM collection: fills in message_<uid>.db (t_buddy → PERSON / t_session → TOPIC / t_message → EVENT, columns device-verified), high-sensitivity → opt-in includeDm:true (off by default), leaving existing posts / likes / follows untouched. Versions: productVersion v5.0.3.130 → v5.0.3.133; pdh 0.4.39 + chainlesschain 0.162.129 published to npm; USR_VERSION 61 / binariesVersion 20260628c.',
  },
  {
    tag: 'v5.0.3.130 · 2026-06-24',
    title: 'Qzone one-tap collection + WeChat Moments collection + §8.3 learning-layer backup on device + personal-assistant UX',
    sub: 'Cumulative v5.0.3.127–130: QQ Zone (Qzone) one-tap collection via an in-app WebView (feed / message board / albums, 404 events on a real device) + WeChat Moments plaintext collection (2824 entries on a real device); §8.3 learning-layer backup commands on device; personal-assistant stuck-watchdog + sticky always-visible trust cards. pdh 0.4.36 + cli 0.162.117 published to npm; Android cc bundle internal-binaries-android-v20260624 (USR_VERSION 58).',
    desc: 'Qzone has no readable local DB → uses the API: new pdh/lib/forensics/qzone-collect.js (g_tk = bkn hash over the qzone-domain p_skey; feed / message board / albums → EVENT) + cc hub collect-qzone; Android "QQ Zone" one-tap card — in-app WebView opens ptlogin2 login (QR / account+password) → captures the qzone p_skey cookie → in-APK cc hub collect-qzone into the device vault (real-device end-to-end: scan to log in → 404 events, 329 feed + 73 board + 2 album). WeChat Moments SnsMicroMsg.db is plaintext SQLite (no key); new parseSnsEvents (SnsInfo → EVENT, body from the protobuf TimelineObject), 2824 entries on a real device. §8.3 learning-layer backup commands on device: cc memory/instinct/learning export/import (hierarchical memory + learned habits + self-evolution trajectories), combined with the vault commands to cover end-to-end encrypted backup of all assets — keys stay personal, never uploaded. Personal-assistant UX: silent stuck-watchdog (20s reassurance / 120s friendly timeout + retry / auto-restart on process exit) + pending trust cards pinned (sticky) so they are no longer scrolled away by the message stream. Versions: productVersion v5.0.3.126 → v5.0.3.130; pdh 0.4.36 + chainlesschain 0.162.117 published to npm; USR_VERSION 58 / binariesVersion 20260624.',
  },
  {
    tag: 'v5.0.3.126 · 2026-06-22',
